{
  "texts": [
    "MRI is used less often to detect pneumonia, but it can provide a detailed image of the lungs and other organs in the chest.",
    "Lung cancerLung cancer can be detected using X-ray images.",
    "An X-ray can reveal abnormal masses or nodules that may indicate a tumor or other abnormality.",
    "Further testing, such as a CT scan, may be preferred to confirm the diagnosis if an anomaly is found.",
    "CT scans are the most commonly used imaging modality."
  ]
}